com.nambimobile.widgets.efab

Class OrientationConfiguration

  • com.nambimobile.widgets.efab.OrientationConfiguration

  • public class OrientationConfiguration

    Holder for all the views of an ExpandableFab widget in a specific enum Orientation. Not meant to be instantiated by clients, as an instance can be retrieved via ExpandableFabLayout.portraitConfiguration or ExpandableFabLayout.landscapeConfiguration. Values for the views will only be populated after they are added through calls to ExpandableFabLayout's addView methods (or after they're defined via XML).

    Implementation Notes:

    1. Since the Kotlin 'internal' modifier translates to 'public' in Java, the JvmSynthetic annotation is used on those functions and properties to hide them from the published API for Java clients. A proper solution to this issue would be a package-private visibility modifier, but Kotlin has yet to implement it (https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/KT-29227). Until then, the JvmSynthetic annotations should remain in order to present the proper published API to both Java & Kotlin clients.

    See Also:
    enum Orientation, ExpandableFabLayout.portraitConfiguration, ExpandableFabLayout.landscapeConfiguration, JvmSynthetic
